JOHANNESBURG - Six suspects are expected to appear in the Johannesburg magistrate s court in connection with the Northcliff murders. They six who face murder, kidnapping and house robbery charges were arrested on Wednesday.The bodies of siblings Gregory and Melanie Naidoo and Melanie s 23-year-old daughter were discovered in Centurion on Monday.READ: Six men expected to appear in court for Northcliff triple murderThey had been burnt beyond recognition.A car belonging to the family and household items were later recovered in Soweto.One of the suspects is believed to be a former employee of the family.eNCA